subSubSection.paragraph:
Chthonius caprai
differs from
C. jonicus
in the following characters: posterior margin of carapace mainly with 6 macrosetae (with 4 macrosetae in
C. jonicus
); no eyes (anterior eyes with flat lens, posterior ones reduced to a pale cuticular area in
C. jonicus
); chelicerae with 1 or 2 lateral microsetae (without lateral microsetae in
C. jonicus
); chela length 0.31–0.43 mm ( 0.40–0.51 mm in
C. jonicus
); movable chelal finger length 0.21–0.28 mm ( 0.275–0.34 mm in
C. jonicus
); movable chelal finger with coupled sensilla pc on a weak tubercle (coupled sensilla pc not on a tubercle in
C. jonicus
).
